# Skywire visor service user — created by systemd-sysusers at
# package install time. Runs the visor when /etc/skywire.conf sets
# SKYWIRE_USER=_skywire (the package default). Underscore prefix
# follows the BSD/Debian convention for service users; avoids
# colliding with the existing `skywire` human user that some
# deployment hosts already have.
#
# Format: man sysusers.d
# u <name> <id> <gecos> <home> <shell>
u  _skywire  -  "Skywire visor service user"  /var/lib/skywire  /usr/sbin/nologin
